-- Migration 031: Add historical context for EFSubMultisig

UPDATE contracts SET
  description = 'One of the earliest multisig governance contracts on Ethereum, written in Serpent by the Ethereum Foundation core team. Deployed August 12, 2015, just 13 days after Frontier launched, by the address Etherscan labels "EF 1" (0x5ed8cee6b63b1c6afce3ad7c92f4fd7e1b8fad9f). The contract implements a simple majority-vote model with three hardcoded signer addresses. Any two of three signers can execute a motion by calling signMotion. If the target address is zero, the motion emits a log event with the data payload instead of sending ETH. The contract was called only three times, all on its deployment day, and holds no remaining balance.',
  historical_significance = 'The first preserved contract deployed by the Ethereum Foundation EF 1 developer wallet, and one of the earliest examples of on-chain multisig governance. Built in Serpent before Solidity was mature, it shows how the core team managed internal authorization in the days immediately following Frontier launch. The 3-of-3 signer structure reflects the cautious governance mindset of the early EF. A twin contract with identical bytecode was deployed 23 minutes earlier at 0x2194b1734ee0f67440884da49952a45b34ba832d, likely a test run before the production deployment. The same EF 1 wallet later deployed the Gamble contract (block 235,543), which has also been bytecode-verified.',
  historical_context = 'Ethereum Frontier launched July 30, 2015. In the first two weeks, core developers deployed foundational infrastructure including wallets, registries, and governance tools. The EF 1 address was one of several EF developer keys active in this period. This multisig appears to have been set up as part of an initial key ceremony. The three signer slots hold cold or hardware wallet addresses with no other on-chain transaction history, held by different EF team members whose identities have not been publicly confirmed. Reading on-chain storage confirms the three signer addresses: 0x23a1bada327be1da636cf6c31f71349e3ea0ba00, 0x288bbeb76a509947f3ea8c56e9b86d81f3b41897, and 0x5ed8cee6b63b1c6afce3ad7c92f4fd7e1b8fad9f.'
WHERE address = '0x209711382eaeb6c1e021e0fc81acc5afa9b23d25';
